From 4f19b36c532f680b86058c3a638ecbc7c011d556 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Andrew Miller <soc1024@illinois.edu>
Date: Sun, 29 Mar 2026 12:57:37 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] CPU-GPU bitwise parity: 100% tensor match for Q4_K_M
 models
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

18 phases of fixes achieving bitwise-identical output between
CUDA GPU (3090/SM86) and x86 CPU for deterministic inference.

Verified: 2462/2462 tensors match, all tokens identical at temp 0.7,
any prompt length, through full autoregressive decode.

Key fixes:
- Portable math: expf_det, sincosf_det, powf_int_det, silu_det
  (CUDA device transcendentals differ from glibc by ±1 ULP)
- RMSNorm: double-buffered butterfly matching GPU warp shuffle,
  __frsqrt_rn replacing approximate rsqrtf, double-precision CPU rsqrt
- Q4_K/Q6_K matmul: explicit FMA matching NVCC auto-fusion patterns,
  warp-parallel accumulation with butterfly reduction
- Flash attention: tile-based softmax with butterfly kqsum,
  FP32 Q·K dot product, direct VKQ/S division (not 1/S * VKQ)
- Q8_1 quantization: x86 SIMD bypass to use roundf(x/d) matching GPU
- Per-column mmvq: forces ncols=1 kernel for batch-size-independent SASS
- Build: -mfma for hardware FMA parity with NVCC auto-contraction

Root causes found:
- Every CUDA transcendental (expf, sinf, cosf, powf, rsqrtf) differs
  from glibc by ±1 ULP — portable implementations needed on both sides
- x86 arch-specific Q8_1 used reciprocal multiply (127/max * x) while
  GPU uses direct division (x / (max/127)) — different rounding
- ptxas JIT generates different SASS per ncols_dst template parameter —
  must force single-column processing for deterministic builds
- GPU attention processes K-V in tiles with warp butterfly reduction;
  CPU must match tile structure, not use sequential online softmax

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
